+# Local Aura-Call Handoff
+
+This README captures the current Aura-Call state on this machine as of
+2026-06-08. It is a local handoff note for continuing work, not the public
+project README.
+
+## Repository
+
+- WSL repo: `/home/bak3r/codex-research/corpora/repos/auracall`
+- Windows path: `\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\bak3r\codex-research\corpora\repos\auracall`
+- Preferred Node runtime:
+
+```bash
+export PATH=/home/bak3r/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/bin:$PATH
+```
+
+## What Works Now
+
+- MCP client/server startup works from WSL with Node 22 through:
+  - `scripts/run-mcporter.sh`
+  - `scripts/run-local-mcp.sh`
+  - `config/mcporter.json`
+- Installed MCP tools include:
+  - `browser_readiness`
+  - `response_read`
+  - `runtime_control`
+  - `windows_powershell_probe`
+- MCP `runtime_control` can participate in the bounded local-action loop:
+  - resolve pending local-action requests
+  - drain a specific run
+  - cancel a run
+  - resume human escalation
+  - repair stale heartbeat leases
+  - claim a local run in a long-lived MCP session
+- The installed MCP server registers a process-scoped local runner:
+  - runner id shape: `runner:mcp-runtime-control:<pid>`
+  - heartbeat TTL: 15 seconds
+  - same-session `claim-local-run` plus `drain-run` was verified.
+- The same-session MCP claim/drain proof is now committed as:
+  - `scripts/smoke-mcp-runtime-control.ts`
+  - `pnpm run smoke:mcp-runtime-control`
+- The installed MCP `windows_powershell_probe` bridge is now covered by a
+  same-session smoke:
+  - `scripts/smoke-mcp-windows-powershell-probe.ts`
+  - `pnpm run smoke:mcp-windows-powershell-probe`
+  - optional live browser check:
+    `pnpm run smoke:mcp-windows-powershell-probe -- --devtools-port 55855`
+- The installed MCP `browser_readiness` gate exposes the same
+  `auracall.browser-doctor` / `auracall.browser-readiness` contract as
+  `auracall doctor --json`:
+  - `scripts/smoke-mcp-browser-readiness.ts`
+  - `pnpm run smoke:mcp-browser-readiness`
+  - default `mode=local` does not launch Chrome or attach to provider pages
+  - `mode=live` is read-only and only probes an already registered managed
+    browser
+- The installed MCP runtime can execute one planned bounded host action through
+  the real local-action path:
+  - `scripts/smoke-mcp-local-action.ts`
+  - `pnpm run smoke:mcp-local-action`
+  - optional WSL-to-Windows PowerShell bridge check:
+    `pnpm run smoke:mcp-local-action -- --windows-powershell-bridge`
+- WSL can talk to Windows PowerShell through:
+  - `scripts/wsl-powershell-chat.sh`
+  - `scripts/windows-powershell-chat.ps1`
+- The machine-local host-action ceiling allows bounded shell actions under the
+  Aura-Call repo root, so allowed local actions can call the WSL-to-Windows
+  bridge without exposing arbitrary PowerShell execution.
+- Windows Chrome launched from WSL is discovered by WSL UNC managed profile
+  path, not by broad first-PID matching.
+- Browser state now rejects stale `windows-loopback` registry entries when the
+  live Windows Chrome process belongs to a different managed profile.
+
