+## MCP Claim/Drain Proof
+
+The strongest MCP runtime-control proof is a same-process MCP SDK stdio smoke,
+not separate one-shot mcporter commands. The passing installed smoke did this:
+
+1. Created a temporary `AURACALL_HOME_DIR`.
+2. Seeded one ordinary direct runtime run with a runnable step.
+3. Started installed `~/.local/bin/auracall-mcp` over stdio.
+4. Called `runtime_control action:claim-local-run`.
+5. Called `runtime_control action:drain-run` on the same MCP connection.
+6. Read `run_status`.
+7. Verified the stored runtime bundle ended `succeeded`.
+
+Observed result:
+
+```text
+claim status: claimed
+drain status: executed
+run_status: completed
+stored bundle status: succeeded
+lease owner: runner:mcp-runtime-control:<pid>
+lease status: released
+step summary: bounded local runner pass completed
+```
+
+## MCP Local-Action Proof
+
+The installed local-action proof starts `~/.local/bin/auracall-mcp`, seeds a
+temporary direct runtime run whose bundle already contains one step-owned
+bounded shell `localActionRequests[]` entry, claims the run through
+`runtime_control`, drains it on the same MCP SDK stdio connection, and verifies
+that the stored run contains the executed local-action result.
+
+Observed result:
+
+```text
+local-action MCP smoke: pass
+tool=runtime_control
+listed=ok
+claim=claimed
+drain=executed
+run_status=completed
+localAction=executed
+stdout=AURACALL_LOCAL_ACTION_OK
+leaseOwner=runner:mcp-runtime-control:<pid>
+leaseStatus=released
+```
+
+The same smoke can execute the WSL-to-Windows PowerShell bridge as the bounded
+local action:
+
+```text
+pnpm run smoke:mcp-local-action -- --windows-powershell-bridge
+mode=windows-powershell-bridge
+powershellStdout=AURACALL_WINDOWS_POWERSHELL_OK
+```
+
+## MCP Windows PowerShell Proof
+
+The installed MCP PowerShell proof starts `~/.local/bin/auracall-mcp`, lists
+tools through one MCP SDK stdio connection, calls `windows_powershell_probe`
+with `probe=get_location`, and verifies that Windows PowerShell returns its
+current path and version. When a managed browser is listening, pass
+`--devtools-port 55855` to also verify that Windows PowerShell can read the
+Chrome DevTools `/json/version` endpoint.
+
+Observed result:
+
+```text
+windows-powershell MCP smoke: pass
+tool=windows_powershell_probe
+listed=ok
+locationPath=<Windows PowerShell cwd>
+powershellVersion=<version>
+devtools=skipped
+```
+
+Observed live browser result with the managed Windows Chrome instance:
+
+```text
+devtoolsPort=55855
+devtoolsBrowser=Chrome/148.0.7778.218
+```
+
+## MCP Browser Readiness Proof
+
+The installed MCP browser-readiness proof starts `~/.local/bin/auracall-mcp`,
+lists tools through one MCP SDK stdio connection, calls `browser_readiness`,
+and validates the structured readiness fields.
+
+Latest installed smoke:
+
+```text
+browser_readiness target=chatgpt mode=local ok=false state=no-live-managed-browser severity=warning requiresHuman=false agentAction=launch-login canDriveBrowser=false
+agentCommand=auracall login --target chatgpt --wait-for-manual-clear auto
+recommendedAction=Run "auracall login --target chatgpt" or start a browser-backed run, then rerun "auracall doctor --target chatgpt".
+```
+
+This is the MCP-facing gate agents should query before browser-backed work. It
+returns an explicit `agentDecision` object so clients know whether browser
+driving is allowed. Cloudflare/CAPTCHA/account-auth pages resolve to
+human-required decisions and do not attempt to solve or click anti-bot
+challenges.
+
+## Current Browser Blocker
+
+`auracall doctor --target chatgpt` now exposes a first-class readiness verdict
+and collects blocking-page evidence in both human and JSON modes. The latest
+local state after pruning the stale browser-state entry is:
+
+```text
+readiness: not-ok (no-live-managed-browser; warning)
+activeManagedInstance: none
+chromeGoogleAccount: Bakermaun@gmail.com
+expectedChatgptIdentity: Bakermaun@gmail.com
+recommendedAction: auracall login --target chatgpt, then rerun doctor
+```
+
+The default runtime profile now has an expected ChatGPT identity configured for
+`Bakermaun@gmail.com`. The managed Windows Chrome profile is not currently
+registered as live. The next step is to relaunch the managed browser, complete
+ChatGPT sign-in as a human if the page shows Cloudflare/CAPTCHA/account auth,
+then rerun doctor/identity smoke before any real browser prompt proof.
+
+Before the stale entry was pruned, the managed tab had reached a logged-out
+ChatGPT landing page. Agent Browser (`agent-browser --cdp 55855 snapshot -i`)
+confirmed visible `Log in`, `Sign up for free`, and a guest textbox; the
+provider account identity was still unavailable. The doctor failed closed as
+`login-required` with `blockingState.kind=account-auth`.
+
+A low-risk CDP reload/focus attempt against the current tab did not clear the
+page: before and after were both `https://chatgpt.com/`, title
+`Just a moment...`, with zero visible buttons, links, inputs, textareas, or
+contenteditable composer nodes.
+After relaunching the managed browser through `auracall login --target
+chatgpt`, the tab advanced to `https://chatgpt.com/auth/login` and doctor now
+classifies it as `login-required`.
+
+A later credential-free CDP click on `Continue with Google` did not reach a
+Google account chooser. The managed tab moved to
+`https://chatgpt.com/api/auth/error`, title `Just a moment...`, with no visible
+controls. The doctor still classifies this as `login-required` with
+`blockingState.kind=account-auth`; the latest snapshot path is:
+
+```text
+/home/bak3r/codex-research/corpora/repos/auracall/auracall-browser-tools-chatgpt-login-required-2026-06-08T23-41-30-582Z.json
+```
+
+After adding the human-clear waiter, `auracall login --target chatgpt
+--wait-for-manual-clear 8` relaunched Windows Chrome on `windows-loopback:55855`.
+Cloudflare cleared without automation, and the selected tab reached
+`https://chatgpt.com/` with title `ChatGPT`. The page is still logged out, so
+`auracall profile identity-smoke --target chatgpt --include-negative --json`
+fails with `chatgpt_identity_not_detected`.
+
+The logged-out ChatGPT landing page is now classified as an account-auth gate.
+A short live check with `auracall login --target chatgpt --wait-for-manual-clear
+3` waited for human sign-in and timed out with `Provider account chooser or
+sign-in gate detected` instead of treating the guest page as ready.
+
+Doctor readiness now also treats a failed/missing browser-tools probe as
+`browser-probe-error` before applying the identity fallback. This prevents
+parallel doctor/setup probe contention from masking a missing browser probe as
+only `identity-unverified`.
+
+`auracall doctor --target chatgpt --json --save-snapshot` now writes a
+browser-tools snapshot even when selector diagnosis is skipped because the page
+is blocked. The snapshot captures the selected URL, page title, visible-control
+counts, cookies/storage samples, and blocking state. The latest snapshot has
+`reason=login-required`, `url=https://chatgpt.com/`, and
+`blockingState.kind=account-auth`.
+
+The doctor still reports that the source browser cookies are newer than the
+managed ChatGPT profile. A pre-cleanup installed doctor proof also reported
+`readiness.state=no-live-managed-browser` because the managed Windows Chrome
+registry entry on `windows-loopback:55855` was stale (`dead-process`), and its
+`recommendedAction` explicitly said to run
+`auracall doctor --target chatgpt --local-only --prune-browser-state` before
+relaunching or starting the login flow. Running that cleanup pruned one stale
+entry. The current next action is to relaunch/login and complete ChatGPT
+sign-in in the managed browser before claiming full browser automation.
+
+Useful readiness commands:
+
+```bash
+auracall doctor --target chatgpt --local-only --prune-browser-state
+auracall doctor --target chatgpt --json --operation-timeout 15
+auracall profile identity-smoke --target chatgpt --include-negative --json
+auracall setup --target chatgpt --skip-login --skip-verify --json
+auracall setup --target chatgpt --skip-login --skip-verify --wait-for-identity auto --json
+auracall login --target chatgpt --wait-for-manual-clear auto
+auracall setup --target chatgpt --wait-for-manual-clear auto --wait-for-identity auto --skip-verify
+```
+
+Use `--wait-for-identity auto` for agent-driven setup or unattended retests. It
+waits up to five minutes for the provider app identity to match the expected
+runtime profile identity. Use `--wait-for-manual-clear auto` only when a human
+is present to clear Cloudflare, CAPTCHA, or account-auth gates in the opened
+browser; Aura-Call observes the page and resumes when the gate clears, but does
+not solve anti-bot challenges.
+
+If a refreshed live browser lands on Cloudflare, CAPTCHA, Google account auth,
+or another human-verification surface, `doctor --json` now reports that under
+`readiness.state` as `manual-clear-required` or `login-required`. A provider
+root tab titled `Just a moment...` is classified as a Cloudflare-style
+manual-clear page even when the body text omits the literal Cloudflare label.
+A logged-out ChatGPT root page with `Log in` and `Sign up` controls is
+classified as `login-required` so the human-clear waiter can hold until sign-in
+is completed.
+
+Useful retry command after clearing the visible browser challenge:
+
+```bash
+auracall --chatgpt \
+  --browser-model-strategy ignore \
+  --prompt "Read the attached package.json and reply with exactly: AURACALL_BROWSER_OK" \
+  --file package.json \
+  --slug auracall-browser-ok \
+  --timeout 180 \
+  --force \
+  --no-notify
+```
+
+If it fails, inspect the stored session through MCP:
+
+```bash
+sh ./scripts/run-mcporter.sh call auracall.sessions limit:5 --config config/mcporter.json
+sh ./scripts/run-mcporter.sh call auracall.response_read id:<session-id> --config config/mcporter.json
+```
+
