new file mode 100644
index 00000000..b7b3e542
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/codex-pro-guard-loop.md
@@ -0,0 +1,93 @@
+# Codex Pro Guard Loop
+
+This loop lets Codex use a browser-backed ChatGPT Pro account as a reviewer
+and grading guard while preserving AuraCall's setup/execution/observation
+boundary.
+
+## Contract
+
+The loop actor is Codex, not `run_status`.
+
+1. Codex makes local changes and runs local verification.
+2. Codex creates one AuraCall reviewer response through MCP `response_create`,
+   HTTP `/v1/responses`, or the CLI.
+3. AuraCall submits the reviewer prompt through the configured ChatGPT browser
+   route and persists the provider response.
+4. Codex polls the same run id with MCP `run_status`, HTTP run status, or CLI
+   run status until terminal.
+5. Codex reads the full persisted response with MCP `response_read`, HTTP
+   `GET /v1/responses/{response_id}`, or the CLI response readback path.
+6. Codex parses the returned verdict and either fixes concrete findings or
+   stops when the guard passes.
+
+Observation surfaces remain read-only. Polling, archive search, and response
+readback must not resubmit prompts, reopen provider workbenches, or navigate
+provider pages.
+
+## Reviewer Request Shape
+
+Prefer a configured Pro-capable agent:
+
+```json
+{
+  "model": "agent:pro-extended-chatgpt-reviewer",
+  "input": "<review prompt>",
+  "runtimeProfile": "wsl-chrome-3",
+  "service": "chatgpt",
+  "transport": "browser",
+  "metadata": {
+    "workflow": "codex-pro-guard",
+    "round": 1
+  }
+}
+```
+
+If a configured agent is not available, use the current ChatGPT browser model
+selector that is known to work for the profile, then keep the same polling
+contract.
+
+## Verdict Shape
+
+The reviewer must return exactly one JSON object:
+
+```json
+{
+  "pass": false,
+  "score": 0,
+  "summary": "one sentence",
+  "blocking_findings": [
+    {
+      "severity": "critical",
+      "file": "src/example.ts",
+      "line": 42,
+      "issue": "specific problem",
+      "required_fix": "specific fix"
+    }
+  ],
+  "nonblocking_findings": [],
+  "tests_or_checks_required": [],
+  "confidence": "medium"
+}
+```
+
+Codex should fail the guard when:
+
+- the verdict is malformed or missing
+- `pass` is not `true`
+- `score` is below 90
+- any `blocking_findings` remain
+- required local tests/checks were not run and no blocker explains why
+
+## Evidence
+
+For auditable workflows, Codex should attach the parsed verdict with
+`run_archive_attach_evidence`, `POST /v1/archive/evidence`, or CLI
+`auracall api archive-evidence`. Use:
+
+- `producer`: `codex-pro-guard`
+- `schema`: `codex.pro_guard.v1`
+- `responseId`: the reviewed AuraCall response id when available
+- `data`: the parsed verdict
+
+This keeps grading/review evidence searchable without making AuraCall core own
+domain-specific correctness.
