+- 2026-06-06: WSL MCP client failures can come from the client and the server
+  inheriting distro Node 18 even when the repo has Node 22 under NVM. Keep
+  mcporter smokes behind `scripts/run-mcporter.sh`, and keep
+  `auracall-local` behind `scripts/run-local-mcp.sh`, so both sides prefer the
+  user Node runtime before falling back to plain `node`.
+
+- 2026-06-06: WSL-to-Windows operator checks need a stateful PowerShell
+  bridge, not repeated ad hoc quoting through nested shells. Use
+  `scripts/wsl-powershell-chat.sh` for one-shot or JSONL stdin/stdout
+  exchanges with Windows PowerShell; keep it local over stdio and do not turn
+  it into a network service.
+
+- 2026-06-06: `setup` must not acquire a managed-profile operation lock and
+  then call login through a second independent file-backed dispatcher for the
+  same profile. Pass a caller-owned/null dispatcher through the login core so
+  setup's exclusive operation covers the browser launch without self-deadlock.
+
+- 2026-06-06: Windows Chrome launched from WSL with a WSL-local managed
+  profile is reported by Windows as a `\\wsl.localhost\<distro>\...`
+  `--user-data-dir`, not a `/mnt/c/...` path. Windows process discovery,
+  DevTools-port discovery, login registration, and browser-service
+  opportunistic registration must match that UNC-normalized profile path
+  instead of falling back to the first `chrome.exe` PID from `tasklist`.
+
+- 2026-06-06: A responsive `windows-loopback` DevTools port is not enough to
+  trust browser-state ownership. If Windows process discovery can identify the
+  requested managed profile, registry liveness must reject a different stored
+  PID as `profile-mismatch`; otherwise stale entries can attach a live port to
+  the wrong Chrome profile.
+
+- 2026-06-06: ChatGPT browser automation can still be externally gated after
+  local setup succeeds. On this machine `auracall setup --target chatgpt
+  --skip-verify` produced a live managed Chrome target, but the first real
+  browser prompt stopped at Cloudflare "Just a moment..."; complete that check
+  in the visible browser before rerunning the prompt.
+
+- 2026-06-06: MCP `response_read` should read durable CLI/browser sessions as
+  a fallback when no response-run record exists for the id. This lets clients
+  use `sessions` to discover a failed/detached browser session and then use
+  `response_read` to fetch the stored log/request without resubmitting the
+  prompt or switching readback tools.
+
+- 2026-06-06: For WSL/Windows host actions, prefer AuraCall's existing bounded
+  shell local-action path over a broad generic PowerShell MCP command. On this
+  machine the host ceiling in `~/.auracall/config.json` allows `sh` only under
+  the AuraCall repo root, so explicitly allowed local actions can call
+  `scripts/wsl-powershell-chat.sh` while retaining command and cwd allowlists.
+
+- 2026-06-06: MCP clients that only need Windows diagnostics should use the
+  constrained `windows_powershell_probe` tool, not a general PowerShell runner.
+  Verified against the installed runtime with `get_location`, `devtools_version`
+  for DevTools port `54759`, and `get_process` for managed Chrome PID `37636`.
+
+- 2026-06-08: MCP clients need a bounded operator-control surface for the
+  agentic local-action loop. Use `runtime_control` for the same service-host
+  controls as `POST /status`: resolve pending local-action requests, targeted
+  drain, cancellation, human-escalation resume, stale-heartbeat repair, and
+  local scheduler claim. The tool must not bypass the run's local-action policy
+  or the host local-action ceiling.
+
+- 2026-06-08: MCP `claim-local-run` must be tested inside one live MCP server
+  process, not with separate one-shot mcporter commands. The installed MCP
+  server now registers a process-scoped local runner with the same short
+  heartbeat TTL used by API/CLI runners; same-session claim plus `drain-run`
+  can claim a direct runtime run for `runner:mcp-runtime-control:<pid>`,
+  release that lease, and complete the run through the bounded local runner.
+  Keep ordinary direct response runs on the runner fallback path by having the
+  configured browser stored-step executor return `undefined` for direct runs
+  that do not declare AuraCall browser execution metadata.
